<paragraph id="8BEF369CE414FFBEF9F960C4FE9F33A0" blockId="18.[151,1436,1532,2025]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B924EA8EE414FFBEF9F960C4FED63337" bold="true" box="[151,320,1532,1557]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Identification.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<number id="3D9824BBE414FFBEFB6B60C5FDB13337" box="[517,551,1533,1557]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="8.5">8.5</number>
–10.0 mm. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D1FE414FFBEFBC660C6FC253337" box="[680,947,1534,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperstrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pervertens">
<emphasis id="B924EA8EE414FFBEFBC660C6FC253337" box="[680,947,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Hyperstrotia pervertens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a light gray, nondescript moth. Forewing with white antemedial and postmedial lines (some specimens may have a thin black line associated with these white lines), reniform spot a small black dot, and outer margin with small dark gray elongate spots. 
<collectingCountry id="F347760CE414FFBEFC67637DFAD7337F" box="[1289,1345,1605,1629]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is light gray.
</paragraph>
